text:
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu visits Manly 0:25 Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu visits Manly while in Sydney
February 24th 2017 2 days ago /video/video.news.com.au/News/ Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu visits Manly Manly Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu visits Manly during Sydney trip John Morcombe, Julie Cross, Sarah Swain and Robbie Patterson, Manly Daily February 24, 2017 5:51pm Robo-poll shows Libs fears of losing Manly MP backs northern beaches tunnel CENTRAL  Manly was shut down this afternoon during a lightning visit by Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu.
media_camera Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu in Manly Picture: John Morcombe
After arriving at Manly Wharf by boat about 3pm, Mr Netanyahu walked along the front of the Manly Wharf Hotel to East Esplanade Reserve, stopping to shake hands with patrons, before crossing East Esplanade and walking up Wentworth St to the beachfront.
media_camera Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu in Manly Picture: John Morcombe
After arriving at the beach, Mr Netanyahu shook hands with a number of locals and tourists, including Victor Dalzell, 70, of The Hills, who was impressed that the Prime Minister had come to Manly with his wife, Sara.
media_camera The Israeli PM took in the sights of Manly Beach. Picture: Adam Yip
“It was lovely seeing him walk around holding his wife’s hand,” he said.
“I recognised him straight away. I put my hand out and he shook it – there was no problem.
“I’ll never forgive my wife for not taking a photo of it.”
media_camera Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu’s whirlwind tour of Australia stopped off at Manly on Friday. Picture: Tom Loomes
But others who saw Mr Netanyahu walking along the street, then the beachfront, clearly didn’t know who he was.
Two excited teenage boys rushed up, thinking the fuss was due to the presence of the Kardashians, but went away disappointed.
media_camera Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu walking along Manly's beachfront. Picture: Julie Cross
Mr Netanyahu visited Manly Wine next to The Sebel.
There was a heavy police and security presence, both on the footpath and on the street. Traffic on East Esplanade, Wentworth St and South Steyne was gridlocked while police cars and motorcycles shut down traffic until Mr Netanyahu had left.
media_camera Netanyahu dined at Manly Wine. Picture: Annika Enderborg
Students of Manly Village Public School ran down to the beachfront to see what was happening as the visit coincided with the close of school for the day.
media_camera Victor and Hazel Dalzell meet Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu on a visit to Manly. Picture: Julie Cross.
Mr Netanyahu was visiting Manly on the third day of a four-day visit to Sydney, during which he has had several meeting with Australian Prime Minster Malcolm Turnbull, and other senior ministers, to discuss trade and security issues.
